The attorney was arrested during an entrapment operation on Friday, when he offered the Hawks a bribe to stop the investigation into his clients. JOHANNESBURG - The Hawks have arrested a 67-year-old attorney in Parktown, Johannesburg, on charges of corruption after he offered police a R50,000 bribe.Sipho Sibiya is allegedly representing five Health Department officials who are being investigated for selling jobs within the department, with prices ranging from R5,000-R6,000.Captain Ndivhuwo Mulamu says during an entrapment operation on Friday, Sibiya offered the Hawks a bribe to stop the investigation into his clients. He appeared before the Johannesburg court yesterday and faces charges of corruption. He was granted bail of R2,000. The case has been postponed to 18 April for further investigation. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)